The `sign_change` function was used to find mean period of IMF. However, I just found a function in scipy which provides an easier solution, and is probably better computationally. Please see if this will be a better solution,
```python
def mean_period(data):
    return len(data)/len(argrelextrema(data, np.greater)[0])
```
The code bassically finds the number of peaks(local extrema) in the signal and divides it from the length of the time-series to estimate the mean period. The same method was also employed by Wu and Huang in their paper.

